Anthrax - Serbia
--------------
Information received on 15 Jul 2013 from Dr Zorica Novakovic, Acting Chief Veterinary Officer, Veterinary Directorate, Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Water Management, Belgrade, Serbia

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification (Final report)
Date of start of the event: 2 Jul 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 5 Jul 2013
Report date: 15 Jul 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 15 Jul 2013
Date event resolved: 5 Jul 2013
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 3 Sep 2012
Manifestation of disease: Sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic), Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Trijebine, Sjenica, Zlatiborski, Serbia
Date of start of the outbreak: 2 Jul 2013
Outbreak status: Resolved (5 Jul 2013)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 1 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 1 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 100.00 percent / 100.00 percent / 100.00 percent / 100.00 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection
* Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures:
Measures applied
* Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s)
* Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)
* No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied
* No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Veterinary Specialized Institute Kraljevo (Regional Reference Laboratory) / Cattle / Ascoli test / 5 Jul 2013 / Positive

Future Reporting:
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations [There is an error in this map as it places Trijebine in Montenegro, though granted very close to the border with Serbia. - Mod.MHJ].

